            "name": "Abraham Lincoln",
            "title": "Republican critic of slavery's expansion",
            "bio": "\"Under a government which imprisons unjustly,\" wrote Thoreau, \"the true place of a just man is also a prison.\" Among the war's critics was Abraham Lincoln, who had been elected to Congress in 1846 from Illinois. Seeking reelection to the Senate as both a champion of popular sovereignty and the man who had prevented the administration from forcing slavery on the people of Kansas, Douglas faced an unexpectedly strong challenge from Abraham Lincoln, then little known outside of Illinois. What enabled Lincoln to emerge as president from the divisive party politics of the 1850s?",
