      "back": "\"In this age of annexation,\" he wondered, \"why not extend the 'area of freedom' by the annexation of California?\" The first part of Mexico to be settled by significant numbers of Americans was Texas, whose non-Indian population of Spanish origin (called Tejanos ) numbered only about 2,000 when Mexico became independent. By 1830, the population of American origin had reached around 7,000, considerably exceeding the number of Tejanos. Anglos (white settlers from the East) and Tejanos had fought together to achieve independence, but soon relations between them soured.",
